    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe annotated [`3.2.7` tag](https://github.com/cython/cython/releases/tag/3.2.7) currently resolves to e8d1e6dba36c8940dc327227c525fb2e7b4a0584 on [`master`](https://github.com/cython/cython/tree/master).\n\nThe release-preparation commit on [`3.2.x`](https://github.com/cython/cython/tree/3.2.x) is 21daa4e0d268fb108419323fe43bd6752d47a130, `Prepare release of 3.2.7`. This [comparison](https://github.com/cython/cython/compare/21daa4e0d268fb108419323fe43bd6752d47a130...e8d1e6dba36c8940dc327227c525fb2e7b4a0584) shows that the tagged commit is 556 commits ahead.\n\nThe attached source distribution and wheels are named `cython-3.3.0a2.dev0`, including [`cython-3.3.0a2.dev0.tar.gz`](https://github.com/cython/cython/releases/download/3.2.7/cython-3.3.0a2.dev0.tar.gz). This appears to confirm that the release workflow built the development branch rather than the intended 3.2.x release source.\n\nThis has already propagated to downstream packaging. conda-forge/cython-feedstock#193 downloads the GitHub tag archive and [published build 0 as Cython 3.2.7](https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/cython/files?version=3.2.7).\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```console\n$ git clone --filter=blob:none https://github.com/cython/cython.git\n$ cd cython\n\n$ git rev-parse '3.2.7^{}'\ne8d1e6dba36c8940dc327227c525fb2e7b4a0584\n\n$ git show -s --format='%H %s' '3.2.7^{}'\ne8d1e6dba36c8940dc327227c525fb2e7b4a0584 Prevent a potential integer overflow in PyArray resizing.\n\n$ git show -s --format='%H %s' 21daa4e0d268fb108419323fe43bd6752d47a130\n21daa4e0d268fb108419323fe43bd6752d47a130 Prepare release of 3.2.7.\n\n$ git rev-list --count \\\n    '21daa4e0d268fb108419323fe43bd6752d47a130..3.2.7^{}'\n556\n```\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nThe `3.2.7` tag should resolve to the intended 3.2.x release commit, and the generated source distribution and wheels should identify themselves as Cython 3.2.7.\n\n### OS\n\nNot applicable - release/tag metadata\n\n### Python version\n\nNot applicable\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.2.7 GitHub tag/release\n\n### Additional context\n\nCould the maintainers confirm the intended corrective action and advise downstream redistributors whether the current `3.2.7` artifacts should be withdrawn?\n",
